On August 14, 2018, the President signed four bills into law:

1. H.R. 2345, the "National Suicide Hotline Improvements Act of 2018," requires the Federal Communications Commission (FCC) to work with the Departments of Health and Human Services and Veterans Affairs to study the possibility of creating a three-digit dialing code for a national suicide prevention and mental health crisis hotline system.

2. H.R. 5554, the "Animal Drug and Animal Generic Drug User Fee Amendments of 2018," reauthorizes FDA user fee programs for animal drugs and animal generic drugs for five years. It also makes amendments to FDA animal drug programs, including electronic submission of applications, drug labeling, conditional approval of drugs, agency guidance on investigational design, food additives, and pet food.

3. H.R. 6414 extends the authority for promulgation of regulations necessary to carry out the tribal transportation self-governance program.

4. S. 770, the "NIST Small Business Cybersecurity Act," requires the Commerce Department's National Institute of Standards and Technology to develop and distribute resources for small businesses to help them reduce their cybersecurity risks.